The House Committee on Regulated Industries offers the following substitute to HB 630:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapters 7A and 47 of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to practice of applied behavior analysis and used motor vehicle and used motor
3 vehicle parts dealers, respectively, so as to revise provisions relating to professional
4 licensure; to revise the definition of "certifying entity"; to remove the used car division and
5 the used parts division of the State Board of Registration of Used Motor Vehicle Dealers and
6 Used Motor Vehicle Parts Dealers; to confer the powers and duties of such divisions to the
7 board; to revise the membership of the board; to revise the powers and duties of the board;
8 to revise and clarify provisions relating to applications for and requirements of licenses; to
9 revise provisions relating to the change of location by licensees; to revise and provide for
10 definitions; to make conforming changes; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting
11 laws; and for other purposes.
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
